              <span id="reviewTextContainer10562978" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9848072557944833461">OK, I&apos;m a sucker for horse books. Ruffian is a good story, about an incredible filly, but not as well written as Seabiscuit: An American Legend. I think part of the problem is that, inspite of her name, Ruffian was a filly whose training and story, while filled with great promise and blistering speed, were mostly uneventful until the bitter end. As a reader and horse lover, I&apos;m left mourning the passing of a racing great whose short career will always be plagued by the question: How much more co</span>
  <span id="freeText9848072557944833461" style="display:none">OK, I'm a sucker for horse books. Ruffian is a good story, about an incredible filly, but not as well written as Seabiscuit: An American Legend. I think part of the problem is that, inspite of her name, Ruffian was a filly whose training and story, while filled with great promise and blistering speed, were mostly uneventful until the bitter end. As a reader and horse lover, I'm left mourning the passing of a racing great whose short career will always be plagued by the question: How much more could she have done?</span>
